<br>
I did my final turn in last night and I can say I love Fluffy!<br>
<br>
Ok, so here’s my Epic quest tale:<br>
<br>
Element of Fire:<br>
Torch of the Elements - (Easy camp when helping my wife get her Chanter Epic, took 4 hours total.)<br>
Blazing Wand - (I actually HAD this piece before I started my Epic from helping a druid friend with the Corrupted Sea horse, but MQ’d it for a Mage friend that was almost done. Thanks Zacatac for the MQ!)<br>
Burning Embers – Ran into Burning Woods, found Neze wandering and killed him. Dropped the Ember first kill!<br>
Power of the Orb – Power of Fire took 4 hours to camp. The hardest part was the 3 day camp to get the Words in Najena! The rest was all up and all dropped off the first mob I killed!<br>
<br>
Element of Earth:<br>
Shovel of Ponz – Had it at level 1 (Twink!)<br>
Broom of Trilon – Had it at level 1 (Twink bastard!)<br>
Staff of Elemental Mastery: Earth – Friend in a 1 group exp hunt in Hate tells you “You need an Earth staff, just got one.” WOOT<br>
Dirt of Underfoot – Walked up, killed Slixin.. looted Dirt.<br>
<br>
Element of Water:<br>
Staff of Elemental Mastery: Water – Worked out a deal with a Mage friend for the staff, dropped off the first Phinny he killed the next day!<br>
Rain of Karana – Hunted Tarbul for 3 days solid! (He spawned once, but was stuck in the mountain!)<br>
Tears of Erollisi – Single pulled Captain Rottgrime at level 51! (Died on first try, got him on second) pwned<br>
<br>
Element of Wind:<br>
Crown of Elemental Mastery – 9 Days on Isle 7 can drive a man quite MAD<br>
Elemental Binder – Dropped like candy in the Hole<br>
Pegasus Feather Cloak – Hunted Quil for 2 days, gave up. Another druid is 10k richer.<br>
<br>
All in all, I would say I spent as much effort on this Epic as I did on my first set of Crafted and Totemic armor. (GOD those quests spoiled the game for me!)<br>
<br>
I know I got lucky on a number of drops, and I’m VERY thankful to all who helped make this dream a reality! Special thanks to Nuitari, Zacatac, Petitioner and of course, My lovely Enchanter wife Kirianna!<br>
<br>
At level 52, this is the most significant upgrade I think I’ll ever get. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
